message.content: Sally has 3 brothers, and each of her brothers has 2 sisters. This means that there are a total of 2*3 = 6 sisters in her family, including Sally. Therefore, Sally has 6 sisters. However, when we ask "How many sisters does Sally have?", it is implied that we are only counting the number of sisters she has excluding herself. In this case, if we exclude Sally from the count, she would have 5 sisters. So, Sally has 5 sisters, excluding herself.
